about.summary: Client library for the Google Ads API

name: google-ads
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "google-ads" %}
{% set version = "11.0.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/google-ads-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 989f0c80ffa7a73c1fe586a31ee6a3ae9c86b92f8ce4d96ec8c982cf8a5d198f
  patches:
   # to stay noarch: python and still pass pip check, we're taking out pep562
    - 0001-remove-pep562-dependency.patch

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.7
    - pip
  run:
    # keeping python above 3.7 so it can stay noarch: python and avoid pep562
    # dependency (only for py<=36)
    - python >=3.7
    - google-api-core >=1.21.0,<2.0.0
    - google-auth-oauthlib >=0.3.0,<1.0.0
    - googleapis-common-protos >=1.5.8,<2.0.0
    - grpcio >=1.33.2,<2.0.0
    - proto-plus >=1.18.0,< 2.0.0
    - pyyaml >=5.1,<6.0
    - setuptools >=40.3.0

test:
  imports:
    - google
    - google.ads
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/googleads/google-ads-python
  summary: Client library for the Google Ads API
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE
  dev_url: https://github.com/googleads/google-ads-python
  doc_url: https://developers.google.com/google-ads/api/docs/start

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - xylar

about.summary: Client library for the Google Ads API
